China Children 's Center will hold a series of activities to let children "high-tech" through "June 1"-Xinhuanet Xinhua Agency, Beijing, May 20 th(Huang Xiaoxi, Zhou Shanshan) The reporter learned from the China Children 's Center on the 20th that the China Children' s Center plans to hold a series of activities such as the Children 's Maker Experience, the Children' s Visual Arts Festival, and the Parent-Child Book Carnival around the Children 's Day from May 28 to June 1, so that children can spend the "June 1" in the charm of cutting-edge technology. It is understood that the activities held by the China Children' s Center during this year 's "June 1" Children' s Day include the "Love Family and Create Cool" Children 's Future Learning Carnival,The first Children 's Visual Arts Festival,"Book Carnival" activities,"Family Love Reading" picture book series activities. Li Zhongming, deputy director of the China Children' s Center, said at the 2016 "June 1" Children 's Day media briefing held on the 20th that "Love the Family and Create Cool" Children' s Future Learning Carnival is a key activity of the China Children 's Center to celebrate "June 1" this year.Through the participation of children and families in various innovative educational activities, innovative practice has become the cultural gene of the general family, and "hands-on" has become a new way of learning and life for the majority of families. It is reported that the "Love Family Create Cool" Children's Future Learning Carnival includes dozens of cutting-edge scientific and technological experience contents, such as "Bean Fruit Maker" experience activity, the anniversary celebration of Lao Niu Children's Exploration Museum and "Exploring the Family Love Children's Love over June 1" activity, VR national experience plan,"Maker Tribe" interactive workshop, etc.
